text.tspan: Out-of-pocket expenditure per capita on healthcare, 2000 to 2015
Out-of-pocket expenditures are defined as direct payments made by individuals to health care providers at the time
of service use. Expenditure per capita is measured in PPP international US$.
Source: WHO Global Health Expenditure Database
